The President of Russia, Vladimir Putin, has signed a law imposing administrative liability for breach of the time and procedure for payment of goods (work, services) in the conduct of procurement for public and municipal needs.
The law is intended to address the very acute problem of the failure of employers to comply with their obligations in public and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation where entrepreneurs could not receive payment under existing government and municipal contracts was widespread.
At the same time, the President of Russia instructed the Office of the Procurator-General of the Russian Federation to take special control of the problem.
Because the businessmen themselves were unable to deal with unfair employers who entered into unfunded contracts, tried to avoid the obligations they had made and included illegal terms in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, in order to protect the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public orders, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office has submitted 9,700 submissions, 4,500 officials have been brought to disciplinary proceedings and 533 administrative officers have submitted 75 submissions to the investigative authorities for the conduct of the investigations, 46 of which have been prosecuted.
As a result, over 66 billion roubles were owed to entrepreneurs.
These enormous amounts have not been accumulated as a result of the non-payment of multi-billion-dollar contracts.
Verbatim debt has resulted in numerous, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs for far more modest amounts.
Here's a special case.
The head of a small company won a competition for social transport services for several million roubles.
A person has invested all his working funds, has fully complied with his obligations, but has not received the money in time.
The result is a growing financial coma of arrears in salaries, taxes, and loans that would have led to bankruptcy if the employer had not sought assistance from the Public Prosecutor ' s Office.
The problem has now been eliminated in a number of regions.
Nevertheless, as of the first half of the year 2017, the total amount of public and municipal debt identified by the prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation was about 27.4 billion roubles.
In regions where debt rates continue to reach critical levels, the Public Prosecutor's Office operates under a manual crisis management.
The Attorney-General personally holds visiting meetings with local authorities, at which all violations revealed by prosecutors and measures to address them immediately are dealt with.
Such operational meetings have already been held this year in Yaroslav and Ekaterinburg.
The implementation of Federal Act No. 189-FZ on the amendment of the Code of Administrative Offences to establish the administrative liability of the employer ' s officials for violating the time and procedure for payment of goods (work, services) in the conduct of the procurement to ensure State and municipal needs will improve the payment discipline of public customers.
The draft law had been drafted by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia at the initiative of the Office of the Attorney-General.
The new law would supplement the Code of Administrative Offences of the Russian Federation with an article which provided for a fine of 30,000 to 50,000 roubles for breach by an official of the employer of the time and procedure for payment of goods, works and services in public and municipal procurement.
If an official has already been subject to administrative punishment for a similar offence, he or she will be disqualified for a period of one to two years.
All prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to ensure the implementation of these legislative innovations in practice.
