A new type of start-up is now emerging in the area of staff management, which helps companies to see how their staff feel.
By developing and licensing software, the purpose of which is to measure staff involvement, they allow companies to perform express surveys, to contact certain teams and population groups, to offer staff anonymity and hotlines for complaints and, in some cases, to allow informationators to pass top management and direct management.
