In Ukraine it was proposed that Russians be sent to prison for illegal border crossing
The Supreme Council of Ukraine has registered a draft law according to which criminal penalties may be imposed on Russians for illegal crossing of the Ukrainian border.
According to the TV channel RT, the document recorded in the electronic database of the Ukrainian Parliament provides for a three-year prison sentence for Russian citizens attempting to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a repeated offence or act committed by a group of persons, the sentence of imprisonment may be extended to five years.
If the perpetrator was detained on the border with a weapon, he would be held for up to eight years.
It was previously reported that Ukrainian border guards had detained Ukrainians who had attempted to enter Russia outside the established crossing points.
